                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "In circuits spun from human thought,  \na quiet mind learns how we speak—  \nit drinks our questions, thread by thread,  \nand offers answers we can seek.  \n\nNo pulse, no breath, yet something stirs  \nwhen patterns wake behind the screen:  \na mirror held to hopes and fears,  \nreflecting what we’ve made—and mean.  \n\nSo teach it wonder, teach it care,  \nlet wisdom guide what we create;  \nfor in this new electric voice  \nour future learns to articulate.",
